Apple today <a href="https://www.apple.com/jp/newsroom/2025/06/apple-introduces-my-number-card-on-iphone/">announced</a> that Japan's My Number Card can now be added to the Wallet app <a href="https://faq.myna.go.jp/faq/show/11995">on an iPhone XS or newer running iOS 18.5 or later</a>.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/06/Apple-Wallet-Japan-My-Number-Card.jpg" alt="" width="1360" height="765" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1007788" /><br/>
The card can be added to the Wallet app via the latest version of the <a href="https://apps.apple.com/jp/app/%E3%83%9E%E3%82%A4%E3%83%8A%E3%83%9D%E3%83%BC%E3%82%BF%E3%83%AB/id1476359069">Mynaportal</a> app, and it can be presented in person or in apps, where accepted digitally.<br/>
<br/>
Starting today, Apple said the My Number Card on the iPhone can be used to print official documents at convenience stores in Japan, and to access the <a href="https://myna.go.jp/">Mynaportal</a> to receive online government services. In the future, users will also be able to present a My Number Card on the iPhone at hospitals and pharmacies in Japan.<br/>
<br/>
Japan is the first country to support the Wallet app's ID feature outside of the United States.<br/>
<br/>
Apple says approximately 100 million people in Japan have a My Number Card.<br/>
<br/>
